# ── Builder Loop Coach — LLM brain (free-LLM survival chain) ─────────────────────
# Set ANY ONE of these and the coach turns on. The /api/copilotkit route tries each
# provider in order and FAILS OVER at stream-init (a free tier 429/413 → next one).
# All are OpenAI-compatible, so one code path serves every provider.
#
# IMPORTANT (learned from agentic-portfolio): the coach does REAL WORK via CopilotKit
# actions = tool-calls. The model MUST (a) emit structured tool_calls and (b) stream
# plain `content`, not `reasoning_content`. Reasoning-class models return 200 and
# render NOTHING. Verified-good: Groq llama-3.3-70b-versatile, Gemini 2.5-flash.
#
# 1) Groq — fastest, clean streaming, solid tools. Best for the chat UI. console.groq.com
GROQ_API_KEY=
# GROQ_MODEL=llama-3.3-70b-versatile

# 2) Google Gemini — biggest free daily quota, no card. aistudio.google.com
GEMINI_API_KEY=
# GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-2.5-flash

# 3) NVIDIA NIM — frontier variety, but tool-capable models are reasoning-class (may
#    render blank in CopilotKit). Override NIM_MODEL with a non-reasoning tool model.
NVIDIA_API_KEY=
# NIM_MODEL=

# 4) OpenAI — paid fallback (gpt-4o-mini: tools + clean streaming).
OPENAI_API_KEY=
# OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini

# ── Safety gate (REQUIRED before any deploy) ─────────────────────────────────────
# This coach is ADULTS-ONLY when using a cloud brain, because conversation leaves the
# device. Until on-device WebLLM lands (see SPEC §4), a deploy MUST set this so only a
# consenting adult can talk to the cloud-backed coach. Unset = local dev only.
COACH_ADULT_TOKEN=
